# auto-api-ruby — Cursor Rules

- Ruby 2.5+, zero dependencies (net/http, json, uri from stdlib)
- AutoApi::Client class, 6 public methods
- Keyword arguments for optional params: get_offers("encar", page: 1, brand: "BMW")
- Returns parsed Hashes, no wrapper objects
- snake_case for everything
- frozen_string_literal: true in every file
- YARD documentation in English
- ApiError and AuthError inherit from StandardError
- All code comments and docs in English

## Key Files

- lib/auto_api.rb — entry point
- lib/auto_api/client.rb — main client (6 methods)
- lib/auto_api/errors.rb — ApiError, AuthError
- lib/auto_api/version.rb — version constant
- auto-api-client.gemspec — gem spec

## Never

- Add gem dependencies
- Create response wrapper classes
- Use monkey patching
- Use camelCase naming
